<plot>Why "Vozes do Medo" (Voices of Fear)? A movie in the form of a magazine, about constrainment, negation, impossibility, apathy. There is no story, only facts which might constitute a story, represented using the most diverse forms of cinema language. An special issue about FEAR. Why this subject? The concerns about freedom, freedom which can not be translated only by mysticism, adventure, pornography, symbolism, and laugh, but only by the whole. How to tell and summarize the plot of "Vozes do Medo"? Face to face to reality. 12 itens, 12 directors, where there a merge is made between cinema-verite and fiction, cartoons and fantastic realism, and an infinity of other tendencies and manifestations of the free speech. A survey about Brazil during the 70s. An experiment about freedom.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?644084</url></doc>
